Ad Text:
Senior Consultant – Operating Model Review

Location: Perth, WA (Onsite only)

Contract: 6 months (with likely 6-month extension)

Cathara Consulting is a leading Australian management and technology consultancy, specialising in business transformation and technology-enabled change. We are seeking a Senior Consultant to join our Perth-based client for an initial 6-month engagement, conducting and facilitating a comprehensive review of their operating model.

This role will suit a strategic thinker with proven expertise in organisational design and operating model transformation, who can deliver actionable insights and guide complex organisations through change.

The Role:

As Senior Consultant, you will:

Analyse the current operating environment, structures, and delivery mechanisms to identify systemic challenges and opportunities.

Provide independent, evidence-based insights into how the client can strengthen its leadership and performance.

Apply systems thinking and organisational design principles to address inefficiencies, duplication, and capability gaps.

Assess internal strengths and external pressures, including emerging trends impacting the operating model.

Develop and test future state operating model scenarios, highlighting trade-offs, risks, and performance implications.

Facilitate workshops and interviews with executives and key stakeholders to shape the future state vision.

Produce a blueprint for the future operating model, supported by rigorous analysis and design principles.

Deliver a practical implementation roadmap that addresses sequencing, change management, and sustainability.

Key Duties & Responsibilities:

Conduct research and analysis of internal and external environmental factors.

Evaluate current operating model maturity and define the future state.

Present alternative operating model configurations and assess resilience through scenario testing.

Provide thought leadership on adaptability, influence, and strategic positioning.

Design and deliver executive-level presentations and recommendations.

Skills & Experience:

Extensive demonstrated experience in operating model design, business transformation, or strategic consulting.

Proven ability to apply organisational design frameworks and systems thinking.

Strong facilitation and stakeholder engagement skills, including experience with executives and senior leaders.

Ability to work autonomously, manage competing priorities, and deliver high-quality outputs.

Proactive problem-solving mindset with a focus on outcomes and value creation.

Other Requirements:

Current National Police Clearance (or ability to obtain).

Full-time onsite presence in Perth (hybrid/remote working is not available for this role).

Are you a strategic thinker with expertise in financial modelling and business case development?

Your new company

You'll be working in a large NSW Government department, supporting their financial and strategic objectives. The role sits within a newly formed hub, where you will be working alongside the Executive Director, Strategy Lead, and a small team of analysts, whilst managing multiple stakeholders.



Your new role

Your role will be heavily involved in business case creation and financial modelling. You will provide detailed financial analysis and insights which will be gathered for use when the organisation applies for grants and funding from NSW Treasury. You will be involved in the following:

Lead a team delivering robust financial analysis for strategic initiatives and funding submissions.
Develop complex financial models, conduct cost-benefit analyses (CBA), and calculate benefit-cost ratios (BCR).
Provide financial insights to shape strategic plans and policy positions.
Ensure consistency and transparency across investment evaluations and submissions.
Collaborate with stakeholders to influence funding decisions and drive public value.


What you'll need to succeed

You'll have the following skills and experience:

Advanced Excel skills and proven experience in financial modelling
CA or CPA accreditation with tertiary qualifications in finance or accounting.
Collaborating on business case creation by utilising advanced analysis and modelling skills
Strong understanding of NSW Treasury guidelines and investment evaluation frameworks.
Ability to translate complex policy into actionable financial insights.
Leadership experience and a passion for mentoring teams.
Highly desirable if you bring experience of business case creation for government organisations.
Must have full Australian working rights and be able to pass a Criminal Record Check


What you'll get in return

This is an exciting and crucial role, where you will be forming the future budgets and the direction of the organisation.
6 month role, with the potential to further extend.
Rate up to $860/day + super.
You will be based in Sydney CBD in modern offices within walking distance of metro, train and bus services.
After the first week, you will be able to work from home 2-3 days/week.


What you need to do now

About Us: 
 
At CleanCo we are delivering clean energy solutions to help our customers thrive in a net zero future.  

We own and operate more than 1GW of low emission energy generation and we are actively growing our portfolio to help propel Queensland’s energy transformation.  

We are a passionate, inclusive team committed to creating a clean energy future for Queensland. If our mission resonates with you, consider a career with CleanCo. 



About the Opportunity: 
 
As Portfolio Definition Lead, you’ll play a key role in translating CleanCo’s strategic and asset-life plans into achievable project portfolios. Based in Brisbane, this permanent role sits within the Enterprise Project Management Office (EPMO) and reports to the EPMO Manager.

You’ll lead the enterprise project prioritisation process, manage portfolio intake, and oversee capacity planning to ensure CleanCo’s resources are focused on delivering the highest strategic value. You’ll work collaboratively across the business to consolidate area-level plans into a cohesive enterprise portfolio, and provide insights through dashboards and reporting to senior and executive leadership.  


About You: 

You bring at least 3 years of PMO experience (ideally within an EPMO) and 4+ years in related business fields. You’re confident in translating strategy into executable programs, and skilled in resource forecasting, scenario modelling, and business analysis. 

You’re detail-oriented, organised, and able to work independently. You communicate clearly across all levels and thrive in stakeholder-rich environments. You hold a university qualification in business, project/portfolio management or a related field. PowerBI experience and certifications such as PRINCE2, PMBOK, MSP or MoP are desirable. 

We encourage applications from neurodivergent people, people with disability, First Nations people, and those from diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds. Adjustments to the recruitment process are available on request.

We understand that work is just one important aspect of our employee’s lives. We offer a range of benefits that support balance and create an engaging workplace, by meeting you at your life and career stage.  
 
Perks and benefits of joining the CleanCo team include:  

• Genuine flex work options – supported hybrid working model 
• A progressive and inclusive culture that reflects our unique identity 
• Opportunities to purchase additional leave 
• Discounted health insurance, Fitness Passport, and health promotion programs 
• Opportunities to save via Salary Sacrificing which may increase your take home pay 
• Wellbeing support via our Employee Assistance Program and Mates in Energy  
membership 
 

CleanCo is a proud 2025 Circle Back Initiative Employer and commit to responding to every applicant.

Senior Machine Learning Engineer
Sydney (Hybrid)
Salary: up to $180k + Shares

Role Overview
A forward-thinking tech team is seeking a skilled Machine Learning Engineer with a strong foundation in data engineering and a passion for building scalable, API-driven solutions. This role involves designing end-to-end ML systems and crafting efficient data pipelines using Python, Databricks, and AWS.

 Key Responsibilities
• ML System Architecture: Design and implement complete machine learning workflows—from data ingestion to model deployment and monitoring.
• Cloud-Based Data Engineering: Build and optimize data pipelines using Databricks and AWS to ensure reliable data flow for ML models.
• Feature Engineering: Transform complex datasets and apply advanced feature engineering techniques to enhance model performance.
• Software Design: Apply robust software engineering principles to ensure maintainable, scalable, and reusable ML codebases.
• API Development: Create and document RESTful APIs using OpenAPI standards for seamless system integration.
• Cross-Functional Collaboration: Partner with data scientists, software engineers, and stakeholders to integrate ML solutions and promote best practices.

Required Skills & Experience
• Degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Engineering, or related field
• Advanced Python skills and experience with libraries like Scikit-learn, Pandas, PySpark
• Hands-on experience with Databricks (Delta Lake, Spark, MLflow)
• Proficiency with AWS services (e.g., EC2, S3, ECS, Lambda)
• Strong understanding of software engineering and object-oriented design
• Experience designing/documenting RESTful APIs with OpenAPI (Swagger)
• Excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities

Preferred Qualifications
• Familiarity with Docker and Kubernetes
• Experience with CI/CD pipelines and MLOps practices
• Solid foundation in statistics, probability, and linear algebra
• Exposure to NLP or computer vision projects

Team Culture & Values
This team values curiosity, creativity, and continuous improvement. They encourage bold ideas, calculated risks, and learning through experimentation. Collaboration, respect, and diversity of thought are central to their approach. If you're passionate about building impactful ML systems and thrive in a dynamic, fast-paced environment, this is the place to grow.

Showcase your market presence and industry expertise to continue driving the success of this critical role for NAB.
Full-time role based in Sydney. 

Our people are customer obsessed. They prioritise the needs and satisfaction of the customer above all else.  Our mindset fosters innovation and creates strong, lasting customer relationships as we strive to be the most customer centric company in Australia and New Zealand. 

In the role of Head of Credit Strategy, you will join NAB’s Economics and Markets Research team in a senior leadership position.  

We are seeking a dynamic and strategic thinker; you will be responsible for leading the Credit Strategy team in delivering timely sectoral and company specific research.

You will work closely as part of the Economics and Markets research team, led by Sally Auld, as well as working with key internal stakeholders – in particular, NAB’s Capital Markets Origination and Distribution team. You will develop robust research and analysis; deliver high quality and compelling presentations and communicate key recommendations to internal and external stakeholders.

Each day, you’ll go above and beyond to: 

Produce detailed credit research relevant to the Australian corporate bond market
Synthesising findings and developing compelling, structured client presentations that clearly articulate key views and recommendations
Sectors covered include Banking, Finance & Insurance, Telcos, Retail, Property
Sectoral analysis will focus on industry drivers and competitive forces, likely trends, threats and opportunities, the impact of the economy and economic policy changes, implications from regulatory changes, ranking of participants and determination of industry benchmarks

This senior role is pivotal in leading client delivery, shaping our FP&A practice, and driving commercial growth. You will work with a diverse portfolio of clients, so the ability to quickly understand new business environments and build trusted relationships is essential.

What do we look for in our people?

At Decision Inc., we look for people who want to fulfil their passion for changing the world with technology and data. No two days are the same. You will be challenged and pushed whilst being nurtured and supported to become a master of your craft. You will participate in interesting internal and client projects across different industries and functions, with the opportunity to think outside the box and develop the technology, analytical and soft skills to be recognised as a top performer in your field.

We are client obsessed, and constantly challenging each other on ways to deliver better outcomes with data. We never lose sight of the bigger picture and have fun along the way.

We like to bring people onboard who reflect our values of being personally invested in the success of our clients, and each other and bringing passion, integrity, collaboration, community, and vision to the way they work. If you are a great listener, a team player, a trusted confidant to your friends, smart and savvy, driven and competitive, love to learn, a connector of people and someone who is searching for purpose in how you can explore making a difference through your work, then the Decision Inc. Australia is your kind of team.

What does Decision Inc. do?

Decision Inc. is a global digital partner that enables businesses to reinvent themselves to realise their full potential.

We deliver agility, resilience, and intelligence to any enterprise, enabling them to adapt quickly and thrive through innovation and opportunity. Our teams have engaged with more than 400 clients globally over the past 15 years, providing them with the expertise to build, operate, and optimise their digital businesses.

We achieve this by leveraging the world's best technology to drive our client's business ambitions forward into tomorrow's reality. These technologies include but are not limited to: Microsoft, SAP, Qlik, Snowflake, Alteryx, Automation Anywhere, and Workday Adaptive Insights.

Our success is ultimately driven by our entrepreneurial culture, industry exposure, and the passion of our people. We have three key cross-functional teams – Functional and Specialist Consulting, Development, and Engineering teams. Based in four global offices, our exceptional consultants focus on delivering value to clients by keeping them at the centre of our service delivery. To find out more about our exciting fast-paced culture visit: Careers at Decision Inc.

About the Opportunity
Job Type: Permanent Application Deadline: 31 October 2025

Title                 Capability Lead - CPO Technology

Department     Corporate Enablers Technology  

Location          Kingswood Fields Office Or Canon Street Office

Reports To       Head of Enterprise Technology - Corporate Enablers

Level                Associate Director

About your role
 

As the Capability Lead – CPO Technology, you will lead the technology capabilities that support our HR function, working in close partnership with the Chief People Officer (CPO), HRIS team, and senior stakeholders to deliver a comprehensive HR technology strategy. You will combine strategic vision, programme and portfolio oversight, vendor management, and hands-on leadership to ensure our HR systems, data, and processes are optimised, future-ready, and aligned with the organisation’s goals.

As part of the Corporate Enablers Technology leadership team, you will build and lead a high-performing team to manage and deliver all aspects of the HR technology portfolio. You will work across multiple functions to ensure CPO technology priorities are fully integrated with wider enterprise initiatives. This includes shaping roadmaps, driving innovation (including AI and automation), resolving complex data challenges, simplifying processes, and delivering measurable business value.

Key Responsibilities

Partner with the CPO, HRIS, and senior stakeholders to shape and deliver a comprehensive HR technology strategy and roadmap.
Lead and manage the HR technology portfolio, ensuring cohesive delivery across platforms, programmes, and projects.
Oversee the adoption, optimisation, and integration of core HR systems, especially Workday, and other key platforms including Cornerstone and Gloat.
Build, develop, and lead a high-performing team to deliver technology solutions and ongoing improvements.
Ensure HR technology integrates seamlessly with enterprise systems and supports reliable, high-quality data and insights.
Drive operational excellence by simplifying processes, optimising costs, and improving system usability.
Identify and implement opportunities for innovation, AI, and automation across HR processes.
Manage vendor relationships, contracts, and performance to maximise value.
Foster strong cross-functional partnerships to align priorities, gain buy-in, and deliver impactful outcomes.

About you

Significant leadership experience in HR technology in complex, global organisations.
Strong track record of partnering with senior HR leaders and leading teams to deliver large-scale technology portfolios and programmes.
Deep understanding of HR processes and operating models, with expert knowledge of Workday and strong experience with platforms such as Cornerstone and Gloat.
Demonstrated ability to manage through a team and deliver results across a complex technology portfolio.
Experience integrating HR systems with enterprise platforms and driving data quality improvement.
Skilled in cost optimisation, vendor management, and contract negotiation.
Proficient in leveraging AI, analytics, and automation in HR contexts.
Excellent stakeholder management, influencing, and facilitation skills.
